    goddess_en: "Vadivudai Amman (Tripurasundari) — 'she of divine beauty,' consort of Adhipureeswarar and the embodiment of Jnana Shakti; one of the 51 Shakti Peetams and chief of the Tondaimandalam Shakti triad. Adi Shankara installed a Sri Chakra to render her serene; a line of Namboothiri families still performs her worship. Devotees offer red silk and jackfruit for wisdom and boons.",
