      { tradition: "other", story: "Kodumudi is a rare TRIMURTI KSHETRAM where Shiva (Magudeswarar), Vishnu (Sarangapani), and Brahma are all enshrined in a single complex — the three cosmic functions worshipped together. Sung by all three Moovar, one of the seven great Kongu-Nadu Shiva temples, it enshrines the serpent Adisesha's worship (relieving his burden of bearing the earth), and Magudeswarar is honoured as the witness of truth, before whom oaths and documents are sworn." }
